there are two steps to the goodwill impairment test 
step one compares the fair value of a reporting unit with its carrying amount  including goodwill 
if the reporting unit s carrying amount exceeds its estimated fair value  it is necessary to perform the second step of the impairment test  which compares the implied fair value of reporting unit goodwill with the carrying amount of such goodwill to determine the amount of impairment loss 
a substantial majority of our goodwill was recorded in connection with our acquisition of hughes communications and was assigned to reporting units of our hughes segment 
