revenue recognition our hughes segment enters into contracts to design  develop  and deliver telecommunication networks to customers in our enterprise market 
these contracts for telecommunication networks require significant effort to develop and construct the network  over an extended time period 
revenue under these contracts is recognized using the percentage of completion method of accounting 
depending on the nature of the deliverables in each arrangement  we recognize revenue under the cost to cost method or the units of delivery method 
under the cost to cost method  sales are recorded equivalent to costs incurred plus a portion of the profit expected to be realized  based on the ratio of costs incurred to estimated total costs at completion 
under the units of delivery method  sales are recorded as products are delivered and costs are recognized based on the expected profit for the entire agreement 
profits expected to be realized on long term contracts are based on estimates of total revenue and costs at completion 
these estimates are reviewed and revised periodically throughout the lives of the contracts  and adjustments to profits resulting from such revisions are recorded in the accounting period in which the revisions are made 
estimated losses on contracts are recorded in the period in which they are identified 
changes in our estimates related to revenue recognition for these contracts could result in significant changes in our revenue or costs  which could be material to our consolidated results of operations 
